                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Pharaphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-05-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 30, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Replying to Mr. Hay’s telegram of May 23, Mr. Conger reports that the Russian
                    minister says he understands that the Russian Government is not opposed to open
                    ports and consulates in Manchuria, but that he can not cooperate with Mr. Conger
                    without instructions from his Government, for which he has telegraphed.)</p>
            </div>
